{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"why should you reset the target and not offset the light from it? resetting the target will break the shadows.","created_at":"2016-11-30T05:46:15.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10229#issuecomment-263788843","id":263788843,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10229","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2Mzc4ODg0Mw==","updated_at":"2016-11-30T05:46:15.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/263788843","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/242577?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/makc","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MjU3Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"makc","type":"User","id":242577,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@makc sorry maybe that comment was unclear. By reset I mean set back to the original (internal) target.\r\n\r\nThe the light is initialized with a target (an Object3D positioned at the origin), however that target's position can't be changed easily (#5555). This lookAt function makes it easy to change the target's position. \r\n\r\nHowever there is also the possibility that the target has been changed to another object in the scene, and to prevent the lookAt function changing the position of this object, a reference to the original target is kept and the target is \"reset\" back to this before looking at the new position. ","created_at":"2016-11-30T09:21:24.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10229#issuecomment-263823333","id":263823333,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10229","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2MzgyMzMzMw==","updated_at":"2016-11-30T09:21:24.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/263823333","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5307958?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/looeee","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzMDc5NTg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"looeee","type":"User","id":5307958,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> set back to the original (internal) target.\r\n\r\nwhich means that, by doing lookat, direct light's shadow camera is no longer looking at the target. which is what I was saying, will break the shadows.\r\n\r\non the other hand, if lookat is supposed to change target, not direction, this makes sense.","created_at":"2016-11-30T13:34:31.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10229#issuecomment-263874362","id":263874362,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10229","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2Mzg3NDM2Mg==","updated_at":"2016-11-30T13:34:31.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/263874362","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/242577?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/makc","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0MjU3Nw==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"makc","type":"User","id":242577,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/makc\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@makc I don't think that is an issue, although admittedly I haven't tested it. But the shadow camera is updated to look at the light target each frame, and resetting the target here just switches the light.target from one Object3D to another. At no point is it missing a target. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar object1 = new Object3D();\r\nvar object2 = new Object3D();\r\nscene.add( object1, object2 );\r\n\r\nobject1.position.set( 100, 100, 100 );\r\nobject2.position.set( -100, -100, -100 );\r\n\r\n\r\n\/\/this light is initialised with a target at (0,0,0)  by default\r\nvar light = new DirectionalLight();\r\nscene.add(light);\r\n\r\n\/\/This is valid, the light and shadow camera should now look at object1\r\nlight.target = object1;\r\n\r\n\/\/Next, the following two lines should be identical in effect:\r\nlight.target = object2;\r\nlight.lookAt( new THREE.Vector3( -100, -100, -100) );\r\n```","created_at":"2016-11-30T14:01:14.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/10229#issuecomment-263880181","id":263880181,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/10229","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI2Mzg4MDE4MQ==","updated_at":"2016-11-30T14:01:14.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/263880181","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5307958?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/looeee","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzMDc5NTg=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"looeee","type":"User","id":5307958,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/looeee\/orgs"}},{"inde